From: Marek Czernohous <marek@czernohous.de>
Date: 2026-05-13
Subject: [PATCH] drm/nouveau/display: reject vblank-IRQ enable on inactive CRTC

nouveau_display_vblank_enable() unconditionally arms the nvif vblank
event mask and returns 0. On NVAC (Tesla / GeForce 9400M) the display
engine produces no vblank events until the first atomic_commit gates
the CRTC on, so a successful enable_vblank()/drm_crtc_vblank_get()
followed by drm_crtc_wait_one_vblank() will stall for the full 1 s
timeout and emit drm_WARN at drm_vblank.c:1320.

fbcon's FBIO_WAITFORVSYNC ioctl routes through this path during early
boot. On the 2009 Mac mini (Macmini3,1) the first userland modeset
arrives ~85 s after drm_fb_helper registers the framebuffer device,
so Plymouth issues ~40 such ioctls in that window. Each prints a full
WARN-with-trace and the boot tuckers along at 1 s per timeout.

Make enable_vblank refuse to arm the event mask while the CRTC state
is not yet committed-active. drm_crtc_vblank_get() then returns
non-zero and drm_client_modeset_wait_for_vblank() skips the wait
silently (drm_client_modeset.c:1329 path).

Reported-on: Apple Macmini3,1 / nouveau / GeForce 9400M (NVAC, Tesla)
Signed-off-by: Marek Czernohous <marek@czernohous.de>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nouveau_display.c | 17 +++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 17 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nouveau_display.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nouveau_display.c
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nouveau_display.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nouveau_display.c
@@ -52,6 +52,22 @@
 {
 	struct nouveau_crtc *nv_crtc;
 
+	/*
+	 * Reject vblank-IRQ enable on a CRTC that has not been
+	 * committed-active yet. nvif_event_allow() would succeed but
+	 * the display engine produces no vblank events until the
+	 * first atomic_commit gates the CRTC on. fbcon's
+	 * FBIO_WAITFORVSYNC ioctl, sent during early boot, would
+	 * otherwise route through drm_crtc_wait_one_vblank() and
+	 * stall there for one second per call, emitting drm_WARN
+	 * at drm_vblank.c:1320. On Mac mini 3,1 / NVAC this fired
+	 * ~40 times per boot. Returning -EINVAL here lets
+	 * drm_client_modeset_wait_for_vblank() skip the wait
+	 * silently in that window.
+	 */
+	if (crtc->state && !crtc->state->active)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
 	nv_crtc = nouveau_crtc(crtc);
 	nvif_event_allow(&nv_crtc->vblank);
 
